VThere's a big question at the center of life
p4
aVin our democracies today:
p5
aVHow do we fight terror without destroying democracies,
p6
aVwithout trampling human rights?
p7
aa(lp8
VI've spent much of my career working with journalists,
p9
aVwith bloggers,
p10
aVwith activists,
p11
aVwith human rights researchers all around the world,
p12
aVand I've come to the conclusion
p13
aVthat if our democratic societies do not double down
p14
aVon protecting and defending human rights,
p15
aVfreedom of the press
p16
aVand a free and open internet,
p17
aVradical extremist ideologies are much more likely to persist.
p18
